            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] rejecting the tribute of Nan Min, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">not providing help to the affairs of the king. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">The gates of our former kings [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">I live in my swaddling clothes (? I am immature- humble speech?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">I look upon the ruler. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">The ruler perhaps will say </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">that if it is like this, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">then this is altars of the soil’s [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] If the lord follows it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">it is the intent of the lord. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">[now] the two lords do not follow it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">will I dare not to travel the road and make an announcement? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">Wu asked xx from Chu: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">in the past Heaven on high was not fair, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en">sending down disasters on us [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en">[...] it is not that among the two cities the resentment is extreme, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en">why should we increase it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.10" xml:lang="en">and annihilate the good relationships between our two cities. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.11" xml:lang="en">The ancients have a saying: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.12" xml:lang="en">when the horse is going to run, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.13" xml:lang="en">if someone attacks him, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-3a.14" xml:lang="en">a disaster will soon come.” </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en">Zhou came to announce: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en">Xx came. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en">Xxxx sent an intimate as envoy to yy(?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en">toiling his daifu, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en">and asked about the route. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en">Xxx, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en">he told me: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en">“You are the deviate son of Zhou [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.9" xml:lang="en">Xx dares to dwell on the banks of my river, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.10" xml:lang="en">saying: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.11" xml:lang="en">‘I must xx and destroy your altars, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-4a.12" xml:lang="en">to enlarge the borders of the Eastern Sea. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en">Heaven (lost?) his fairness, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en">humiliating the former kings of Zhou (?) [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en">You have (used) the rewards of carriages and garments, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en">and the threat of capital punishment, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en">and by means of the former and the latter </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en">you have still not been able to use them to rule the people, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en">and on the contrary you want those below (the people) to help you, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-5a.8" xml:lang="en">is this not wrong! </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en">He cut him off between the Po and Tao rivers (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en">[...] the country of the relatives on my mother’s side, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en">and assist the descendants of Zhou, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en">it is the only thing considered ritually appropriate by me. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en">To appease the heart and soften the worries, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-6a.6" xml:lang="en">it is my parental uncle. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-6a.7" xml:lang="en"> </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-7a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] Therefore he used it to send his three ministers, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-7a.2" xml:lang="en">not daring to delay, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-7a.3" xml:lang="en">daring to announce it to the emperor (?). </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-8a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] answered: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-8a.2" xml:lang="en">“the three daifu brought shame on my servant (?). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-8a.3" xml:lang="en">I [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-8a.4" xml:lang="en">? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-8a.5" xml:lang="en">the fortune of the former kings, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-8a.6" xml:lang="en">the divine power of the son of Heaven. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-8a.7" xml:lang="en">Why should I labor? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-8a.8" xml:lang="en">I dare to bring to the outmost the fortune of the former kings, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-8a.9" xml:lang="en">the divine power of the son of Heaven. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-8a.10" xml:lang="en">The people of Wu xx [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-9a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] in Zhou. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-9a.2" xml:lang="en">I asked my aides: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-9a.3" xml:lang="en">“Who will be the chief of the army </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-9a.4" xml:lang="en">and trample the land of Chen? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-9a.5" xml:lang="en">Because the state of Chen is not other </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0072_tls_001-9a.6" xml:lang="en">than the city of the great consort name Yi, related on the female side to the former kings. ??? </seg>
                </p>

         </div>
